      <h2>Specifications</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>Type</th><td>Quick change rotary handpiece</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Collet Size</th><td>3/32&Prime; (2.35 mm) shank</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Collet Release</th><td>Lever action &mdash; 90&deg; rotation</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Shaft Type</th><td>Key Tip</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Compatible Motors</th><td>SR, TX, LX (key tip shafting)</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Variants</th><td>H.20 (standard), H.20D (duplex), H.20SJ (slip joint for European motors)</td></tr>
          <tr><th>Replacement Collet</th><td>HP3-1008 (includes 1.5 mm hex key)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Safety Instructions</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Never turn the collet release lever while the flexible shaft is rotating.</strong> The release lever is not intended for use as a brake. Turning it during rotation can cause damage and extensive wear to the handpiece.
      </div>

      <div class="warning">
        Keep a 3/32&Prime; shank bur in the handpiece at all times during operation and storage.
      </div>

      <ul>
        <li>Always wear proper eye protection while using this handpiece.</li>
        <li>Always make sure your power tool is unplugged during any maintenance procedure.</li>
        <li>Wait for the motor, flexible shaft, and accessory to come to a <strong>complete stop</strong> before turning the lever to open the collet and remove or insert a bur.</li>
        <li>Please read all instructions before attaching this handpiece.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Attaching the Handpiece</h2>

      <div class="note">
        Shaft and sheath connection instructions do not apply to the H.20SJ slip joint handpieces for use with European style motors.
      </div>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h20/p01_02.jpg" alt="Keyed tip on end of shaft and inside back end of handpiece, showing 3/4 inch extension" />
        <figcaption>The keyed tip of the flexible shaft should extend 3/4&Prime; beyond the end of the sheath</figcaption>
      </div>

      <p>The handpiece is easy to remove from the flexible shaft. To remove, simply pull the handpiece off the shaft and sheath with a firm grip. To re-attach, look into the back end of the handpiece for the keyway. Be sure that the key tip of the flexible shaft is properly lined up with the keyway slot in the back end of the handpiece and push it on. If it is not in line, turn the shaft tip or the handpiece to the correct position.</p>

      <h2>Shaft and Sheath Adjustment</h2>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h20/p01_04.jpg" alt="Diagram of sheath, shaft, set screw, motor connector, motor coupling, and motor shaft" />
        <figcaption>Flexible shaft assembly showing sheath, shaft, set screw, motor connector, motor coupling, and motor shaft</figcaption>
      </div>

      <p>It is important to check the sheath and shaft tip and properly adjust them before attaching this handpiece to your Foredom flex shaft tool. The tip of the flexible shaft should extend 3/4&Prime; beyond the end of the sheath.</p>

      <ol>
        <li>Make sure the motor and shaft/sheath are hanging fully extended or laying on a flat surface.</li>
        <li>Loosen the set screw in the motor connector.</li>
        <li>Move the sheath in or out until the shaft tip extends 3/4&Prime; beyond the end of the sheath.</li>
        <li>Tighten the set screw in the motor connector.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Operation</h2>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h20/p01_05.jpg" alt="Handpiece held in hand with lever visible and bur inserted" />
        <figcaption>The H.20 Quick Change handpiece with lever action collet release</figcaption>
      </div>

      <p>This Quick Change handpiece has a unique lever action for collet release to make rapid accessory changes.</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Open collet:</strong> Turn lever 90&deg; to left or right to open collet and release bur.</li>
        <li><strong>Close collet:</strong> Center lever to close collet and secure bur.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h20/p01_09.jpg" alt="Handpiece with bur mounted and lever in closed position" />
        <figcaption>Lever centered to close collet and secure bur</figcaption>
      </div>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Never turn collet release lever while flexible shaft is rotating!</strong> This can cause damage and extensive wear to the handpiece.
      </div>

      <h2>Collet Replacement and Adjustment</h2>

      <p>Tools required: soft jaw pliers, 1.5 mm hex key (included with replacement collet HP3-1008).</p>

      <h3>Removing the Collet</h3>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h20/p01_13.png" alt="Fig. 1 &mdash; Nose-cone, felt washer, lever, and spindle labeled" />
        <figcaption>Fig. 1 &mdash; Unscrew and remove nose-cone and felt washer</figcaption>
      </div>

      <ol>
        <li>Unscrew and remove the nose-cone and felt washer (Fig. 1).</li>
        <li>Open the collet completely, with lever perpendicular (at a 90&deg; angle) to the handpiece (Fig. 1).</li>
        <li>Insert the 1.5 mm Allen wrench into the collet lock screw, and grip the exposed spindle using soft jaw pliers. Turn the Allen wrench counterclockwise 1/4 turn to loosen the collet lock screw (Fig. 2).</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h20/p01_08.png" alt="Fig. 2 &mdash; Soft jaw pliers gripping spindle while Allen wrench loosens collet lock screw" />
        <figcaption>Fig. 2 &mdash; Grip the exposed spindle with soft jaw pliers and loosen the collet lock screw with the 1.5 mm Allen wrench</figcaption>
      </div>

      <ol start="4">
        <li>For collet adjustment only, proceed to Step 7. To replace the collet, or to remove it for cleaning, unthread the collet completely by turning it counterclockwise (Fig. 3).</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h20/p01_07.jpg" alt="Fig. 3 &mdash; Collet being unscrewed counterclockwise from spindle" />
        <figcaption>Fig. 3 &mdash; Unthread the collet completely by turning counterclockwise</figcaption>
      </div>

      <h3>Installing a Collet</h3>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h20/p01_03.png" alt="Fig. 4 and 5 &mdash; Collet with lock screw positioned 5mm from end, and Allen wrench with collet lock screw" />
        <figcaption>Fig. 4 &amp; 5 &mdash; The collet lock screw must be threaded into the collet to a depth of approximately 5 mm (3/16&Prime;) from the back end</figcaption>
      </div>

      <ol start="5">
        <li>When reinstalling a collet or installing a new collet, the collet lock screw must be in the collet before you screw the collet into the spindle (Fig. 5). The collet lock screw must be threaded into the collet to a depth of approximately 5 mm (3/16&Prime;) from the back end of the collet (Fig. 4).</li>
        <li>Check to ensure that the collet release lever is in the fully open position (Fig. 1). Screw the collet into the spindle while gripping the exposed spindle with your fingers. Do not screw the collet in too far. (Do not close the three slots in the collet.)</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Collet Adjustment Procedure</h3>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h20/p01_12.png" alt="Fig. 6 &mdash; Collet adjustment, rotating clockwise to tighten, counterclockwise to loosen" />
        <figcaption>Fig. 6 &mdash; Rotate the collet clockwise to tighten, counterclockwise to loosen</figcaption>
      </div>

      <ol start="7">
        <li>Insert a bur with a 2.35 mm shank into the collet. If the bur does not enter the collet, unscrew the collet counterclockwise until the bur fits in freely, and reinsert the bur. The collet tension is adjusted by rotating the collet clockwise to tighten and counterclockwise to loosen (Fig. 6). The collet is adjusted properly when a <strong>slight</strong> resistance is felt when moving the bur in and out with the collet release lever in the fully opened position. Next, grip the spindle with the soft jaw pliers and tighten the collet lock screw securely with the Allen wrench (Fig. 2).</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h20/p01_11.png" alt="Fig. 7 &mdash; Testing collet holding strength by pulling bur &mdash; no slip" />
        <figcaption>Fig. 7 &mdash; Test the collet&rsquo;s holding strength by trying to pull the bur out with the lever closed &mdash; it should not slip</figcaption>
      </div>

      <ol start="8">
        <li>Insert a 2.35 mm shank bur into the collet and close the collet release lever. Using a cloth to protect your fingers, try to pull the bur out to test the collet&rsquo;s holding strength (Fig. 7). If you can remove the bur by hand, the collet is too loose. If the collet is too loose, loosen the collet lock screw, refer to the Collet Adjustment Procedure above and re-adjust the collet until the bur cannot be removed with the collet closed.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Maintenance and Lubrication</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        Bearings in these handpieces do not need lubrication. Putting oil or grease into the front or back of these handpieces will damage their pre-lubricated ball bearings.
      </div>

      <h3>H.20D Duplex Connection</h3>
      <p>The H.20D duplex handpiece connection should be lubricated approximately every 20 hours of use. Apply 2 drops of oil (p/n MS10005) in the oil hole on the rear of the duplex connection.</p>

      <h3>Flexible Shaft Cleaning and Lubrication</h3>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-h20/p01_10.jpg" alt="Flexible shaft removed for cleaning, with screwdriver and set screw visible" />
        <figcaption>Flexible shaft removed from sheath for cleaning and lubrication</figcaption>
      </div>

      <p>Should be done every 50 hours of use:</p>

      <ol>
        <li>Unscrew the motor connector (left hand thread) and remove the drive shaft.</li>
        <li>Thoroughly clean the flexible shaft with a solvent.</li>
        <li>Apply a <strong>light film</strong> of Foredom grease (p/n MS10006) to the entire length of the inner shaft.</li>
        <li>Reconnect the shaft (see shaft and sheath adjustment instructions above) and sheath, and run the motor for ten minutes before reconnecting the handpiece.</li>
        <li>Turn off the motor, wipe off excess grease from the tip of the drive shaft, and reconnect to the handpiece per instructions.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Repair Service</h2>
      <p>Factory repairs are done promptly and at reasonable cost. Send your equipment directly to the factory marked &ldquo;Attention: Service Department.&rdquo; Be sure to give your street address. The equipment should be accompanied by a brief note describing the problem. Estimates will be made upon request.</p>

      <h2>Warranty</h2>
      <p>Foredom&reg; warrants the Quick Change Handpiece against defective material and workmanship for a period of 90 days from date of purchase. Please return it to the factory for inspection and repair. The duplex connection is particularly susceptible to damage and is not covered by warranty. Replacement duplex springs are shipped with installation instructions.</p>
      <p>This warranty does not cover damage caused in transit or by accident, misuse, or ordinary wear.</p>
      <p>All warranty repairs must be done at the factory: The Foredom Electric Company, 16 Stony Hill Rd, Bethel, CT 06801, (203) 792-8622.</p>
